Then someone before you took that engine out, apart, and put it back  
together using type 1 engine screws. I
see it all the time.

You can just about know a type 4 engine has not been screwed with  
when you see it still has all its original
cheesehead screws.  When I see all straight slot screws, I cringe  
knowing it is a basketcase inside. Ususally
the case says GEX under the tin......


